[[Image:RedBullRampage.jpg|frame|right|Red Bull Rampage logo]] The '''Red Bull Rampage''' is an invitation-only [[freeride]] [[mountain bike]] competition held near [[Zion National Park]] in [[Virgin, Utah|Virgin]], [[Utah]], [[United States]], just to the north of Gooseberry Mesa. Since 2001 till 2004, it was held off the Kolob Terrace Road, on the western boundary of Zion National Park.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://www.descent-world.co.uk/DWR_B4_2005/html/news/news2004/RedBullRampage2004.htm|title=Mountains, Mud and Mayhem ar Red Bull Rampage 2004|website=www.descent-world.co.uk|access-date=2016-05-12}}</ref><ref>https://www.redbull.com/us-en/history-of-red-bull-rampage-with-kyle-strait</ref>
==History== The competition was held since 2001 till 2004 and then canceled due to the increasing risk competitors were taking. After a three-year hiatus, Rampage returned in 2008 with a new venue.<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=http://www.redbull.com/us/en/bike/stories/1331747714648/the-return-of-rampage-2008|title=Rampage Came Back Bigger, Badder in 2008|last=Berard|first=Mike|website=www.redbull.com|access-date=2016-05-12}}</ref> For the 2008 event wooden features have been introduced to what has previously been a "natural" only course.<ref name=":1" />
The competition is usually held in October. The event is similar to [[freestyle skiing]] and [[freestyle snowboarding|snowboarding]], where competitors are judged on their choice of lines down the course, their technical ability and the complexity of tricks. Red Bull Rampage has become one of the biggest mountain biking events of the year.<ref name=":2">{{Cite web|url=http://www.redbull.com/en/bike/stories/1331577024959/relive-red-bull-rampage-2010-with-this-documentary|title=Relive Red Bull Rampage 2010 with this documentary|last=Abrams|first=Amah-Rose|website=www.redbull.com|access-date=2016-05-12}}</ref>
At the first ever Rampage in 2001, the prize money for the event was $8,000. In 2015, the total prize fund was $100,000.<ref name=":8">{{Cite web|url=http://www.pinkbike.com/news/5-things-you-need-to-know-red-bull-rampage-2015.html|title=5 Things You Need To Know - Red Bull Rampage 2015 - Pinkbike|website=Pinkbike|access-date=2016-05-12}}</ref>
